article.headline: Siena 68, Manhattan 64
article.story: NEW YORK -- Edwin Ubiles scored 21 points and Kenny Hasbrouck added 17 to help Siena hold off Manhattan 68-64 on Sunday. Ronald Moore added 13 points for the Saints (12-5, 6-0 Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference), who have won seven of their last eight games. Chris Smith scored 14 points and Devon Austin and Darryl Crawford each had 13 for the Jaspers (9-7, 3-3). Ubiles scored eight first-half points and Siena took a 31-25 lead at the break. Austin's basket with 14:56 left in the game cut the deficit to 43-41, but Manhattan got no closer. The Saints responded with a 14-3 scoring run, capped by Hasbrouck's 3-pointer that pushed the lead to 57-44 with 10:53 remaining. Crawford converted two free throws with 17.2 seconds left to cut the lead to 66-64, but Ubiles responded with two free throws with 14.4 seconds to go to seal the win.
